<paragraph id="936436F7FFD82709FF09FF3B1024DDC6" blockId="7.[136,1452,158,437]" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FF09FF3B1240DD72" bold="true" box="[189,348,230,256]" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">Observations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="54DB4D74FFD82709FE34FF3B118FDD72" authorityName="E. H. Souza &amp; Leme" authorityYear="2021" box="[384,659,230,256]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Cryptanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lutandensis">
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FE34FF3B118FDD72" box="[384,659,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">Cryptanthus lutandensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the morphologically closest relative of 
<taxonomicName id="54DB4D74FFD82709FBC1FF3A16BBDD72" authority="Leme (2002 a: 87)" authorityName="Leme" authorityPageNumber="87" authorityYear="2002" box="[1141,1447,230,257]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Cryptanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reisii">
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FBC1FF3A17CCDD72" box="[1141,1232,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">C. reisii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F74A4B06FFD82709FB6CFF3A16BBDD72" author="Leme, E. M. C." box="[1240,1447,230,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="186" pagination="86 - 90" refId="ref7666" refString="Leme, E. M. C. (2002 a) Two new sympatric Cryptanthus species. Cryptanthus Society Journal 17: 86 - 90." type="journal article" year="2002">Leme (2002a: 87)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species known from Atlantic Forest fragments in the lower elevated region of Itapetinga, 
<collectingRegion id="511FF815FFD82709FB14FED717F9DD56" box="[1184,1253,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">Bahia</collectingRegion>
. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName id="54DB4D74FFD82709FA26FED61217DD3A" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Cryptanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lutandendis">
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FA26FED61217DD3A" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">C. lutandendis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="54DB4D74FFD82709FD23FEF211E8DD3A" authorityName="Leme" authorityYear="2002" box="[663,756,303,329]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Cryptanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="186" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reisii">
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FD23FEF211E8DD3A" box="[663,756,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">C. reisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its distinctly caulescent habit, 
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FB31FEF21783DD3A" box="[1157,1183,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">ca</emphasis>
. 
<quantity id="54239B12FFD82709FB04FEF317E5DD3B" box="[1200,1273,302,329]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="186" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
high (
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FAFDFEF21690DD3A" box="[1353,1420,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">vs. ca</emphasis>
. 
<quantity id="54239B12FFD82709FA29FEF213B6DD1F" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="186" unit="cm" value="7.0">7 cm</quantity>
high) with a larger number of leaves (
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FDDCFE8E1196DD1E" box="[616,650,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">ca.</emphasis>
15 
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FD0CFE8E101DDD1E" box="[696,769,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">vs. ca.</emphasis>
8), shorter leaf blades, sepals with narrowly lanceolate and acuminate lobes (
<emphasis id="A1AFEAE5FFD82709FEFAFEAA1270DDE2" box="[334,364,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="186">vs.</emphasis>
suborbicular, obtuse to slightly cucullate), which are longer and narrower, and petals completely white without greenish apex with acute apex, not emarginate.
</paragraph>
